exif:ImageDescription: Protestors of the "Patriotic Europeans Against the Islamisation of the Occident" (PEGIDA) demonstrate in Dresden, eastern Germany, on December 22, 2014. A new record of more than 17,000 anti-Islamic protesters rallied for their tenth "Monday demonstration" in a row in eastern Germany, celebrating the rise of their far-right movement by singing Christmas carols as about 4,000 counter-demonstrators marched through the city under the slogan "Dresden Nazi-free". AFP PHOTO / DPA / KAY NIETFELD   GERMANY OUT
